W

WHITESPACE - Static variable in class de.brands4friends.daleq.core.internal.formatting.MarkdownTableFormatter
 
with(Row...) - Method in interface de.brands4friends.daleq.core.Table
Adds rows to the table.
withRowsBetween(long, long) - Method in interface de.brands4friends.daleq.core.Table
Adds rows with all ids in the interval [from,to] to the table.
withRowsUntil(long) - Method in interface de.brands4friends.daleq.core.Table
Deprecated.
The method was supposed to be used for convenience, but meanwhile we learned that it is not intuitive. On one hand it is not a good idea to start ids form 0, because some DBs treat 0 as an id special, especially in combination with sequences. For instance, Mysql will not let you explicitly set a a field, which has the auto increment attribute, with a zero, only non zero values could be set explicitly. On the other hand, specifying the maxId as an exclusive interval is not intuitive in this context. Use Table.withRowsBetween(long, long) instead.
withSomeRows(Iterable<Long>) - Method in interface de.brands4friends.daleq.core.Table
Adds rows with the given ids to the table.
withSomeRows(long...) - Method in interface de.brands4friends.daleq.core.Table
Adds rows with the given ids to the table.
